\par\pard\plain \li950\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0 To compile to e-book format:}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-490\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Edit or remove the dedication page contained inside the Front Matter\\E-Book folder. Feel free to add any other front matter documents as required.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Import a cover image (the recommended size is 600x800 pixels, preferably in JPG or PNG format). You can store this anywhere, but it makes sense to place it in the \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93E-Book\u8221\'94 front matter folder. A placeholder cover image is already provided\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 you will want to delete that once you have imported your own.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Go to File > Compile\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Select \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93E-book (with Parts)\u8221\'94 from the \u8220\'93Format As\u8221\'94 menu button if it is not already selected.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-490\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl0{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Expand the window to show all the compile options by clicking the blue arrow button to the right of the \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Format As\u8221\'94 menu button.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-490\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 If you have front matter documents other than the cover image, ensure that the \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Add front matter\u8221\'94 option is ticked and select the \u8220\'93E-Book\u8221\'94 folder from the menu button next to it if it is not already selected. If you don\u8217\'92t have any front matter documents, you can un-tick \u8220\'93Add front matter\u8221\'94. (This does not affect the cover image.)}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-490\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl0{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 If you have imported your own cover image, be sure to click \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Cover\u8221\'94 in the left sidebar and select the image from the \u8220\'93Cover Image\u8221\'94 menu button.}
\par\pard\plain \li1440\fi-490\sl360\slmult1\qj\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 From the \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Compile for\u8221\'94 menu button, choose whether to export to EPUB or Kindle format.}
\par\plain \ilvl1{\listtext\f2\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u9675\'3F	}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 Click \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93Compile\u8221\'94.}
